  id: GER-007
  owner: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3ac2f6537cb4f47de9ff07e3f1784aeb, type: 2}
  title: The Seventh Morning
  proseShort: The morning Margery died. Bread on the counter. A photograph by the
    bed.
  proseFull: A Sunday. The light through the bedroom window is the same light that
    has been there for thirty-six years. Margery's breath is quiet, then quieter.
    Gerrold says her name once. The bread Doris brought yesterday is still on the
    counter. The wedding photograph by the bed catches the light. Gerrold sits in
    the chair beside her for a long time. He does not move when the light changes.
  primaryTone: 1
  secondaryTone: 4
